race.description: G'day G'day From Great Northern Brewery Handicap (55)
race.comment: Very even. PUROSANGUE (1) has the wide gate to overcome but will find this much easier than recent assignments. has good early speed and expected to take catching. ZAVEGA (11) was too quick on debut in easier grade, leading throughout for a dominant win. This tougher but has upside and can give a sight again. PRINCE OF DIAMONDS (3) finished out of the money two starts back then he got a long way back and was beaten 4.5 lengths when fourth over 1200m at this track three-and-a-half weeks ago. Finds an easier assignment and can turn things around. GALLERY MASTER (6) has a good record at the courser and distance. Fitter for two runs in and looks ready to win. HUSSON'S REVENGE (5) was in the money two starts back at Ballina but couldn't back it up last time when sixth, beaten 5.5 lengths, at Gatton over 1400m. Will give a start but wind up late.
